# orchestrator-desktop — Tauri + React

## Layout
```
src/
  api/           client.ts (IPC), types.ts (DTOs)
  ui/            React components + hooks (see ui/README.md)
src-tauri/src/
  main.rs        Tauri commands
  core_bridge.rs Java process, stdin/stdout IPC, core_event
  java_runtime.rs spawn core, PATH/JAVA_HOME
  java_env.rs    Java 17+ validation
```

## IPC flow
React `api.*` → `invoke("core_request")` → CoreBridge → Java → response / log events via `useCoreEvents`.

Contract table: repo `docs/reference/IPC.md`. Integration flow: `docs/integration/INTEGRATION.md`.

## Rust notes
- `core_bridge`: single session mutex for request lifecycle; recv timeout kills JVM; one retry on shutdown/transport errors
- stdout reader: `read_until` + `from_utf8_lossy` (not line iterator)
- Core not started in Tauri `.setup`
- stderr trace: `ORCHESTRATOR_CORE_TRACE=1`, log file `desktop-logs/core.stderr.log`

## Dev commands
| Command | Effect |
| --- | --- |
| `npm run dev` | Vite only |
| `npm run dev:full` | Maven JAR + Vite + tauri dev (same as `scripts/unix/start.sh`) |
| `npm run verify:core-ipc` | Smoke test against JAR |

`devUrl` must stay `http://127.0.0.1:5173`; Vite `--host 127.0.0.1`.

## Hooks
See `src/ui/README.md`. App.tsx uses `useWorkspaceData`, `useServiceFilters`, `useCoreEvents`, `useServiceBranchPolling`, `useServiceShortcuts`, `useJavaRuntime`.

## API client
- `core()` serializes IPC in a queue (Windows safety)
- Branch polling: `useServiceBranchPolling` + `listServiceBranches`
- Tauri-only: folder pickers, `get_runtime_settings`, `set_java_runtime_path`

## Build
```bash
npm run build
cd src-tauri && cargo check
```

Full desktop bundle: `scripts/unix/build.sh` / `scripts/windows/build.ps1`.
